.SH EXAMPLES
Basic usage \[en] parse \[lq]tomorrow\[rq]:
.IP
.EX
td tomorrow \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
Custom output format:
.IP
.EX
td \[dq]next friday\[dq] \-f \[dq]%Y\-%m\-%d\[dq] \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
Apply a specific timezone:
.IP
.EX
td \[dq]now\[dq] \-t UTC \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
Parse an epoch timestamp:
.IP
.EX
td \[at]1719244800 \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
JSON output:
.IP
.EX
td tomorrow \-\-json \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
Batch mode (one expression per line from pipe):
.IP
.EX
printf \[dq]tomorrow\[rs]nnext week\[rs]n\[dq] | td \-f \[dq]%Y\-%m\-%d\[dq] \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
Deterministic output with \[en]now:
.IP
.EX
td \[dq]in 3 days\[dq] \-\-now 2025\-01\-01T00:00:00Z \-f \[dq]%Y\-%m\-%d\[dq] \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Date arithmetic:
.IP
.EX
td \[dq]tomorrow + 3 hours\[dq] \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Boundary expression (end of day):
.IP
.EX
td eod \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Operator\-prefixed offset:
.IP
.EX
td \-\- +3h \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z \-t UTC
.EE
